title: 1_Serum_0Gy
extract_protocol_ch1: Blood samples were collected at pre-specified timepoints via venipuncture. Samples were centrifuged and frozen to -80oC within 4 hours of collection. Exosomes were isolated from selected serum samples using the Qiagen miRCURY Exosome Serum/Plasma Kit. Total RNA was isolated using the Qiagen miRNeasy Serum/Plasma Kit.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: After RNA extraction, small RNA-seq (next generation sequencing) indexed sequencing libraries were prepared from 200 ng total RNA according to QIAseq miRNA Library Kit Handbook (version 11/2016).
data_processing: Adapter trimming and quality filtering (at level 30) was performed using fastp (https://academic.oup.com/bioinformatics/article/34/17/i884/5093234).
data_processing.1: UMI extraction and deduplication was performed with umi_tools (https://genome.cshlp.org/content/early/2017/01/18/gr.209601.116.abstract) using following regex expression: .+(?P<discard_1>AACTGTAGGCACCATCAAT)(?P<umi_1>.{12})(?P<discard_2>.+)
data_processing.2: Mapping to miRbase mature (version 22) was perfomed using bowtie (https://genomebiology.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/gb-2009-10-3-r25) and allowed for 1 mismatch.
data_processing.3: Created bam files were sorted and indexed using samtools (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21903627) and then picard (https://broadinstitute.github.io/picard/).
data_processing.4: Files with counts were collected to table. Counts were converted to TPM and log10 transformed (logTPM) using edgeR without library normalization and prior equal 0.001 (hence -3 as minimum). This utlized OmicSelector (https://biostat.umed.pl/OmicSelector).
contact_department: Department of Biostatistics and Translational Medicine

data_processing.1: UMI extraction and deduplication was performed with umi_tools (https://genome.cshlp.org/content/early/2017/01/18/gr.209601.116.abstract) using following regex expression: .+(?P<discard_1>AACTGTAGGCACCATCAAT)(?P<umi_1>.{12})(?P<discard_2>.+)
data_processing.2: Mapping to miRbase mature (version 22) was perfomed using bowtie (https://genomebiology.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/gb-2009-10-3-r25) and allowed for 1 mismatch.
data_processing.3: Created bam files were sorted and indexed using samtools (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21903627) and then picard (https://broadinstitute.github.io/picard/).
data_processing.4: Files with counts were collected to table. Counts were converted to TPM and log10 transformed (logTPM) using edgeR without library normalization and prior equal 0.001 (hence -3 as minimum). This utlized OmicSelector (https://biostat.umed.pl/OmicSelector).
contact_department: Department of Biostatistics and Translational Medicine

data_processing.3: Created bam files were sorted and indexed using samtools (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21903627) and then picard (https://broadinstitute.github.io/picard/).
data_processing.4: Files with counts were collected to table. Counts were converted to TPM and log10 transformed (logTPM) using edgeR without library normalization and prior equal 0.001 (hence -3 as minimum). This utlized OmicSelector (https://biostat.umed.pl/OmicSelector).

Exosomes were isolated from selected serum samples using the Qiagen miRCURY Exosome Serum/Plasma Kit. Total RNA was isolated using the Qiagen miRNeasy Serum/Plasma Kit.
extract_protocol_ch1.1: After RNA extraction, small RNA-seq (next generation sequencing) indexed sequencing libraries were prepared from 200 ng total RNA according to QIAseq miRNA Library Kit Handbook (version 11/2016).
data_processing: Adapter trimming and quality filtering (at level 30) was performed using fastp (https://academic.oup.com/bioinformatics/article/34/17/i884/5093234).
data_processing.1: UMI extraction and deduplication was performed with umi_tools (https://genome.cshlp.org/content/early/2017/01/18/gr.209601.116.abstract) using following regex expression: .+(?P<discard_1>AACTGTAGGCACCATCAAT)(?P<umi_1>.{12})(?P<discard_2>.+)
data_processing.2: Mapping to miRbase mature (version 22) was perfomed using bowtie (https://genomebiology.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/gb-2009-10-3-r25) and allowed for 1 mismatch.
data_processing.3: Created bam files were sorted and indexed using samtools (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21903627) and then picard (https://broadinstitute.github.io/picard/).
data_processing.4: Files with counts were collected to table. Counts were converted to TPM and log10 transformed (logTPM) using edgeR without library normalization and prior equal 0.001 (hence -3 as minimum). This utlized OmicSelector (https://biostat.umed.pl/OmicSelector).
contact_department: Department of Biostatistics and Translational Medicine
